  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,3,"Brothers and sisters, I will now present the General Authorities, Area Seventies, and General Officers of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints for your sustaining vote."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,4,"Please express your support in the usual way. If there are those who oppose any of the proposals, we ask that you contact your stake president."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,5,"It is proposed that we sustain Russell Marion Nelson as prophet, seer, and revelator and President of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints; Dallin Harris Oaks as First Counselor in the First Presidency; and Henry Bennion Eyring as Second Counselor in the First Presidency."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,6,Those in favor may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,7,"Those opposed, if any, may manifest it."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,8,It is proposed that we sustain Dallin H. Oaks as President of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles and Jeffrey R. Holland as Acting President of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,9,"Those in favor, please signify."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,10,Any opposed may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,11,"It is proposed that we sustain the following as members of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles: Jeffrey R. Holland, Dieter F. Uchtdorf, David A. Bednar, Quentin L. Cook, D. Todd Christofferson, Neil L. Andersen, Ronald A. Rasband, Gary E. Stevenson, Dale G. Renlund, Gerrit W. Gong, Ulisses Soares, and Patrick Kearon."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,12,"Those in favor, please manifest it."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,13,Any opposed may so indicate.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,14,"It is proposed that we sustain the counselors in the First Presidency and the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles as prophets, seers, and revelators."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,15,"All in favor, please manifest it."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,16,"Contrary, if there be any, by the same sign."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,17,"The following General Authority Seventies will be released from their assignments and given emeritus status,effective on August 1, 2025: Elders David S. Baxter, Randall K. Bennett, Kevin S. Hamilton, Rafael E. Pino, and Jorge F. Zeballos."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,18,Those who wish to express gratitude to these brethren and to their wives and families for their years of dedicated service throughout the Church may do so by the uplifted hand.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,19,"We also release Elder José A. Teixeira from serving as a member of the Presidency of the Seventy, effective on August 1, 2025."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,20,Those who wish to express appreciation to Elder Teixeira for his service in this capacity may do so.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,21,We note with gratitude the 65 Area Seventies who will complete their service and whose names can be found on the Church’s website.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,22,Those who wish to join in expressing appreciation to these brethren and to their families for their years of selfless service may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,23,"We extend releases to the Young Men General Presidency, effective on August 1, 2025, as follows: Steven J. Lund as President, Bradley R. Wilcox as First Counselor, and Michael T. Nelson as Second Counselor."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,24,All who wish to join in expressing appreciation to these brothers for their devoted service may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,25,"It is proposed that we sustain Elder Kevin R. Duncan as a member of the Presidency of the Seventy, effective on August 1, 2025."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,26,Those in favor may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,27,Any opposed may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,28,"It is proposed that we sustain the following as new General Authority Seventies: John D. Amos, Ronald M. Barcellos, Steven C. Barlow, Kevin G. Brown, B. Corey Cuvelier, Michael Cziesla, James E. Evanson, Brik V. Eyre, Ozani Farias, Aaron T. Hall, Brian J. Holmes, Pedro X. Larreal, Clement M. Matswagothata, Eduardo F. Ortega, Edward B. Rowe, and Wan-Liang Wu."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,29,"All in favor, please manifest it."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,30,"Those opposed, by the same sign."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,31,"We note that 78 new Area Seventies were sustained during the general conference leadership meetings on Thursday, April 3, and then announced on the Church’s website. We invite you to sustain these brethren in their new assignments."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,32,"Those in favor, please manifest it."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,33,"Any opposed, by the same sign."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,34,"It is proposed that we sustain the following as the new Young Men General Presidency, effective on August 1, 2025: Timothy L. Farnes as President, David J. Wunderli as First Counselor, and Sean R. Dixon as Second Counselor."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,35,Those in favor may manifest it.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,36,Any opposed may so signify.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,37,"It is proposed that we sustain the other General Authorities, Area Seventies, and General Officers as presently constituted."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,38,All in favor may do so by the uplifted hand.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,39,"Those opposed, if any."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/11oaks,President Dallin H. Oaks,40,"Thank you, brothers and sisters, for your sustaining vote on behalf of the leadership of the Church."
