  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,63,"Joseph Smith Translation, Matthew 25:12 (inMatthew 25:12, footnotea)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,64,"Of the parable of the ten virgins, Elder David A. Bednar taught:"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,65,“Please think of the lamps used by the virgins as the lamps of testimony. The foolish virgins took their lamps of testimony but took no oil with them. Consider the oil to be the oil of conversion. …
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,66,"“Were the five wise virgins selfish and unwilling to share, or were they indicating correctly that the oil of conversion cannot be borrowed? Can the spiritual strength that results from consistent obedience to the commandments be given to another person? Can the knowledge obtained through diligent study and pondering of the scriptures be conveyed to one who is in need? Can the peace the gospel brings to a faithful Latter-day Saint be transferred to an individual experiencing adversity or great challenge? The clear answer to each of these questions is no.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,67,"He went on to explain that we have an “individual responsibility to keep our lamp of testimony burning and to obtain an ample supply of the oil of conversion. This precious oil is acquired one drop at a time—‘line upon line [and] precept upon precept’ (2 Nephi 28:30), patiently and persistently. No shortcut is available; no last-minute flurry of preparation is possible” (“Converted unto the Lord,”EnsignorLiahona, Nov. 2012, 109)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,68,"Doctrine and Covenants 33:17. President Russell M. Nelson has counseled: “Now is the time for you and for me to prepare for the Second Coming of our Lord and Savior, Jesus the Christ. Now is the time for us to make our discipleship our highest priority” (“The Lord Jesus Christ Will Come Again,”Liahona, Nov. 2024, 121)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,69,"The sculptor ofFive Wise Virginsis artist Ben Hammond, who portrayed the five wise virgins as women of various ages and racial backgrounds, representing the diversity of women who are converted disciples of Jesus Christ."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,70,"When we partake of the sacrament, we renew all the covenants we have made with the Lord and make a new covenant that we are willing to take upon us the name of Jesus Christ and obey His commandments. Worthy participation in priesthood ordinances and making and keeping covenants make us whole. This principle is beautifully expressed in the sacrament hymn “Bread of Life, Living Water”:"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,71,"Bread of Life, Living Water,"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,72,"Feed my soul, fill my heart."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,73,"Lord, give me new life in Thee"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,74,And make mewhole—complete and holy—
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,75,Bound to Thee eternally.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/14johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,76,"(Hymns—For Home and Church, Gospel Library; emphasis added.)"
