  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/24roman,Elder Sandino Roman,50,"“The Hebrew word for faith isאמונה(emunah) and is an action oriented word meaning ‘support.’ … [It] places the action on the one who ‘supports God.’ It is not a knowing that God will act, but rather I will do what I can to support God. This idea of support for the wordemunahcan be seen inExodus 17:12. … It is the support/emunahof Aaron and Hur that held [up] Moses’ arms, not the support/emunahof Moses. When we say, ‘I have faith in God,’ we should be thinking, ‘I will do what I can to support God’” (Jeff A. Benner, “Faith,” Ancient Hebrew Research Center, ancient-hebrew.org)."
