  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/42shumway,Elder Steven D. Shumway,43,"In the Savior’s parable of the talents, the Master gives responsibility over “a few things” to each servant. The Master was more focused on each servant’s progress toward becoming masters “over many things” and less concerned with the return of His goods. The one servant who was afraid and unwilling to labor was left condemned and without progression. (SeeMatthew 25:14–28.)"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/42shumway,Elder Steven D. Shumway,44,"SeeLuke 21:19. Elder David A. Bednar teaches that “righteous work is a necessity for spiritual progress” (“Things as They Really Are 2.0” [worldwide devotional for young adults, Nov. 3, 2024], Gospel Library)."
