  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,30,"2 Nephi 25:23."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,31,"Omni 1:26."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,32,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 64:34."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,33,"Dallin H. Oaks, “The Desires of Our Hearts” (Brigham Young University devotional, Oct. 8, 1985), 6, speeches.byu.edu."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,34,"Doctrine and Covenants 137:8."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,35,"Doctrine and Covenants 137:9. “That judgment will consider not only your actions, but also your innermost intent and heartfelt desires. … The Lord knows the desires of our hearts. At the time of judgment, surely the special yearnings of single sisters and childless couples, for example, will be given compassionate consideration by Him” (Russell M. Nelson, “Choices,”Ensign, Nov. 1990, 75)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,36,"Doctrine and Covenants 124:49; emphasis added."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,37,"Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Lorenzo Snow(2012), 130."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/44causse,Bishop Gérald Caussé,38,"2 Nephi 25:23."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,4,"Years ago, our early-morning gospel class memorized Bible verses. Naturally I was drawn to short passages. This includedJohn 11:35—the shortest verse in scripture, only two words—“Jesus wept.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,5,"For me now, that Jesus weeps in sorrow and joy testifies of the miraculous reality: the divine Son of God came into physical mortality and learned according to the flesh how always to be with and bless us."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,6,"When we cry out in grief or joy, Jesus Christ understands perfectly. He can be present in the moments when we most need eternity’s great gifts: Jesus Christ’s Atonement, Resurrection, restoration."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,7,"Mary and Martha weep for their brother Lazarus, who has died. Moved with compassion, Jesus weeps. He raises Lazarus to life."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,8,"Jesus beholds Jerusalem on the eve of the Passover. He weeps, unable to gather His people as a hen would her chicks.Today His Atonement gives us hope when we sorrow for what could have been."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,9,"The Lord of the vineyard weeps as He asks His servants, which could include us as ministering brothers and sisters, “What could I have done more for my vineyard?”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,10,"Mary stands bereft at the sepulchre. Jesus gently asks, “Why weepest thou?”He knows “weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning.”Resurrection brings dawn for all."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,11,"In Book of Mormon lands, as the faithful multitude arises to Him, Jesus’s joy is full. He weeps."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,12,"“And he took their little children, one by one, and blessed them, and prayed unto the Father for them."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,13,“And when he had done this he wept again.”
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,14,"This is Easter in Jesus Christ: He answers the longings of our hearts and the questions of our souls.He wipes away our tears,except our tears of joy."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,15,"When our tears flow, we sometimes apologize, embarrassed. But knowing that Jesus Christ understands life’s pains and joys can give us strength beyond our ownas we navigate bitter and sweet."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,16,"In South America, a father sobs. A sparkle in his life, his young daughter, has died. “I would give anything to see her again,” he cries in my arms. I cry too."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,17,"At the Puebla Mexico Temple dedication, tears of happiness wet the face of a dear sister. Her features radiate faith and sacrifice. She says, “Todos mis hijos están aquí en el templo hoy”—“All my children are here in the temple today.” Generations gathered in the house of the Lord bring tears of joy and gratitude."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,18,"In cruel civil war, families and neighbors did unspeakable things to each other. Bitter tears are slowly giving way to hope. Her voice trembling, a woman in a small village says, “Neighbor, before I go to my grave, I want you to know where to find your missing family members.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,19,"A radiant bride and handsome groom are being sealed in the house of the Lord. She is 70 years old, as is he. A beautiful bride, she has worthily waited for this day. She shyly swishes her bridal dress this way, then that way. We shed joyful tears. God’s promises are fulfilled. His covenants bring blessings."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,20,"While home teaching a widowed sister, a young Boyd K. Packer learned a tender lesson. Following a disagreement with her husband, the sister had called out a final hurtful remark. An unexpected accident took her husband’s life that day. “For fifty years,” the widow sobbed, “I’ve lived in hell knowing that the last words he heard from my lips were that biting, spiteful remark.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,21,"Easter in Jesus Christ helps us mend, reconcile, make right our relationships, on both sides of the veil. Jesus can heal grief; He can enable forgiveness. He can free us and others from things we or they have said or done that otherwise bind us captive."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,22,"Easter in Jesus Christ lets us feel God’s approbation. This world tells us we are too tall, too short, too wide, too narrow—not smart, pretty, or spiritual enough. Through spiritual transformation in Jesus Christ, we can escape debilitating perfectionism."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,23,"With Easter joy, we sing, “Death is conquered; man is free. Christ has won the victory.”Christ’s Resurrection frees us from death, from time’s frailties and physicality’s imperfections. Jesus Christ’s Atonement also restores us spiritually. He bled from every pore, weeping blood as it were, to provide us escape from sin and separation. He reunites us, whole and holy, with each other and God. In all good things, Jesus Christ restores abundantly—not only what was but also what can be."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,24,"Jesus’s life and light testify of God’s love for all His children. Because God our Father loves all His children in every age and land, we find His loving invitation to come find peace and joy in Him in many traditions and cultures. Wherever, whenever, whoever we are, we share divine identity as children of the same Creator. In similar spirit, followers of Islam, Judaism, and Christianity share religious heritage in Father Abraham and covenant connection through events in ancient Egypt."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,25,Father Abraham came to Egypt and was blessed.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,26,"Joseph, sold into servitude in Egypt, knew Pharaoh’s dream meant seven years of plenty followed by seven years of famine. Joseph saved his family and his people.Joseph wept when he saw God’s larger plan,where all things work together for good for those who keep their covenants."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,27,"Moses, raised in Egypt in Pharaoh’s household, received and later restored the keys for the gathering of God’s children."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,28,"Fulfilling prophecy, Joseph, Mary, and the infant Christ child sought refuge in Egypt.In Cairo, a devout Muslim believer reverently says: “The Quran teaches that Joseph, Mary, and the baby Jesus found safety and sanctuary in my country. In my country, Jesus as a toddler ate our food, took His first steps, said His first words. Here in my country, we believe trees bent low to give Him and His family fruit. His being in my country blessed our people and land.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,29,"God’s plan of moral and mortal agency allows us to learn by our own experience. Some of our greatest life lessons come from things we would never choose. In love, Jesus Christ descended below and ascended above all things.He rejoices in our divine capacities for creativity and delight, kindness without hope for reward, faith unto repentance and forgiveness. And He weeps in sorrow at the enormity of our human suffering, cruelty, unfairness—often brought by human choice—as do the heavens and the God of heaven with them."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,30,"Each Easter spring season testifies that spiritual sequence and convergence are both part of the divine pattern of atonement, resurrection, and restoration through Jesus Christ.This sacred and symbolic convergence comes not by accident or coincidence. Palm Sunday, Holy Week, and Easter celebrate Christ’s Atonement and Resurrection. As today, every April 6 we commemorate the establishment and organization of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.This Restoration is a reason we gather the first Sunday each April in general conference."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,31,"Restoration also came as the resurrected Jesus Christ, Moses, Elias, and Elijah returned priesthood keys and authority at the newly dedicated Kirtland Temple on Easter Sunday, 1836.In that setting on that day to the restored Church of Jesus Christ came God’s authority and blessings to gather His children, prepare His children to return to Him, and unite families for eternity. Restoration that day fulfilled prophecy by occurring both on Easter and Passover."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,32,"Including the Kirtland Temple, I recently visited sacred places in Ohio where the Prophet Joseph and others saw in vision God our Father and His Son, Jesus Christ. The Prophet Joseph saw what heaven is like. In heaven, Heavenly Father, through Jesus Christ, “saves all the works of his hands”in a kingdom of glory.The only exceptions are those who willfully “deny the Son after the Father has revealed him.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,33,"As His mortal ministry began, Jesus declared His mission to bless us each with all we are willing to receive—in every time, every land, every circumstance. After fasting 40 days, Jesus went into the synagogue and read, “The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he hath anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor; he hath sent me to heal the brokenhearted, to preach deliverance to the captives, and recovering of sight to the blind, to set at liberty them that are bruised.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,34,"Poor, brokenhearted, captive, blind, bruised—that’s each of us."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,35,"The book of Isaiah continues the Messianic promise of hope, deliverance, assurance: “Appoint unto them that mourn in Zion, … give unto them beauty for ashes, the oil of joy for mourning, the garment of praise for the spirit of heaviness.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,36,"Thus, we cry out, “I will greatly rejoice in the Lord, my soul shall be joyful in my God; for he hath clothed me with the garments of salvation, he hath covered me with the robe of righteousness.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,37,"Each Easter season, we celebrate, as a symbolic whole, eternity’s great gifts through Jesus Christ: His Atonement; His (and the promise of our) literal Resurrection; Restoration of His latter-day Church with priesthood keys and authority to bless all God’s children. We rejoice in the garments of salvation and the robe of righteousness. We shout, “Hosanna to God and the Lamb!”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,38,"“For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.”"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,39,"May we each find in Jesus Christ atonement, resurrection, and restoration—peace, becoming, and belonging—that which is enduringly real and joyful, happy and forever, I pray in His holy name, Jesus Christ, amen."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,40,Notes
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,41,"SeeAlma 7:11–12. Note also the covenantal promise in the sacrament ordinance: We take upon us the name of Jesus Christ, “always remember him and keep his commandments … ; that [we] may always have his Spirit to be with [us]” (Doctrine and Covenants 20:77)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,42,"SeeJohn 11:33–35, 39–44."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/45gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,43,"SeeLuke 19:41–44; see alsoMatthew 23:37;Luke 13:34."
