  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/52strong,Elder Michael B. Strong,47,"The police officers put me in jail as part of their standard procedure for an accident resulting in a fatality. They separated me from my companion because I was the driver. I was in the jail for two days. During the police investigation, they discovered that this young man was intoxicated at the time of the accident and that this likely contributed to his sudden turn in front of our moving vehicle. I appeared before a judge for a formal hearing, where it was determined that there was no evidence of fault or negligence but rather that this was simply an unfortunate and tragic accident."
