  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,39,"I testify that Jesus Christ, the Redeemer of Israel, leads this, His Church. He is preparing to come again. May we likewise prepare to receive Him. For this I pray in the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,40,Notes
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,41,"The little stone that the prophet Daniel saw in his dream of the latter days is rolling forth to fill the world (seeDaniel 2:31–45;Doctrine and Covenants 65:2)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,42,"Doctrine and Covenants 121:45."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,43,"“For I will go before your face. I will be on your right hand and on your left, and my Spirit shall be in your hearts, and mine angels round about you, to bear you up” (Doctrine and Covenants 84:88)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,44,"Doctrine and Covenants 121:45, emphasis added; see alsoverse 46."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,45,"Russell M. Nelson, “Peacemakers Needed,”Liahona, May 2023, 98."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,46,Choosing to contend with others is choosing to live without the guidance of the Holy Ghost.
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,47,"We are to have charity “towards all men, and to the household of faith” (Doctrine and Covenants 121:45)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,48,"This means praying “with all the energy of heart” (Moroni 7:48)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,49,"SeeMoroni 7:48."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,50,"SeeIsaiah 9:6."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,51,"As Joseph Smith taught, “If [we] wish to go where God is, [we] must be like God, or possess the principles which God possesses” (Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Joseph Smith[2007], 72). Likewise, the Apostle Paul gave the admonition that we should “come boldly unto the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need” (Hebrews 4:16)."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,52,"SeeMatthew 24:36–37."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,53,"Malachi 4:5; see alsoZephaniah 1:14–18."
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,54,"The Lord has told us to “remember faith, virtue, knowledge, temperance, patience, brotherly kindness, godliness, charity, humility, [and] diligence” (Doctrine and Covenants 4:6). When we do, our confidence will increase, and then, in His own words, when we ask, we shall receive. And when we knock, it shall be opened unto us. (SeeDoctrine and Covenants 4:7.)"
  2025,"04",/general-conference/2025/04/57nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,55,"We may experience what King Benjamin’s people did: “They were filled with joy, having received a remission of their sins, and having peace of conscience, because of the exceeding faith which they had in Jesus Christ” (Mosiah 4:3)."